                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.151/37: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-06-06T13:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 6, 1925—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>222. Department’s telegram 176, June 6, 1 p.m., to Ambassador at London will be
                    repeated to you by Embassy for your information. That telegram instructs the
                    Ambassador to make informal inquiries at the British Foreign Office regarding
                    the assent of the British Government to the pledging by Greece of security in
                    connection with the proposed loans for construction by Ulen and Company of
                    waterworks for Athens and Piraeus.</p>
                <p>Please make similar informal inquiries at the French Foreign Office.</p>
                <p>Reply by telegraph.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
